While his teammates and friends were snoring during the Bafana Bafana camp in the wee hours of Friday last week, Orlando Pirates defender Thabo "Festival" Matlaba was allegedly busy beating up women and threatening them with a gun. Matlaba, 30, escaped arrest after his ex-girlfriend withdrew charges of common assault she had pressed against him. He was accused of spoiling Charleen Magagula's festive mood at an event in a swanky Sandton nightclub on Friday morning last week. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD